To terminate a C program, you can use the exit() function from the stdlib.h library. This function is safe and legal to use. Here's an example of how to use it:

```c
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    // Your code here
    exit(EXIT_SUCCESS);
}
```

In this example, we include the stdlib.h library and call the exit() function with the parameter EXIT_SUCCESS. This will terminate the program and return an exit status of 0, indicating successful execution.

